  "texts": [
    "These staining artifacts ranged from inadequate labeling of the cell nuclei (due to weak binding with hematoxylin) to insufficient coloring of cytoplasmic and extracellular regions (due to weak binding with eosin).",
    "Given the suboptimal staining quality in these regions, they could not be effectively employed as references (ground truth) for evaluating the quality of our virtual staining results.",
    "Consequently, it became imperative to distinguish between fields-of-view (FOVs) with high staining quality and those with staining artifacts before embarking on further steps of this evaluation process.",
    "To achieve this, we established an image feature-based staining artifact identification process.",
    "To begin with, we divided all ten WSIs of the autopsy test samples into ~2000 FOVs, each corresponding to an area of 1.3 × 1.3 mm 2 (8000 × 8000 pixels)."
  ],
